        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Pope Francis will be officially farewelled and laid to rest. Credits: AAP/Alessandra Tarantino/AP
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Pope Francis lies in repose inside St. Peter’s Basilica, where Vatican residents and members of the papal household have been privately paying their respects. His coffin will be closed Friday evening ahead of Saturday’s funeral, which will take place in St. Peter’s Square.<p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        The Vatican confirmed that 130 delegations will attend the service, including 50 heads of state and 10 reigning monarchs. Among those expected are Donald Trump, Emmanuel Macron, Volodymyr Zelensky, and UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres. Prince William will represent his father, King Charles, who will not attend the service due to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-04-2025-h1-1-royal-protocol?source=website" target="_blank">royal protocol</a>. Vladimir Putin will be absent, as he remains susceptible to an ICC arrest warrant (see the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="http://ps-25-04-2025-h1-2-confirmed-list" target="_blank">confirmed list</a> so far).</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">After the funeral, the coffin will be taken to the Roman Basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore, where he will be entombed, as the Pope <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-25-04-2025-h1-3-chose-to-be-buried?source=website" target="_blank">chose to be buried</a> at the smaller basilica. In keeping with Pope Francis's embrace of the marginalized, the Vatican announced that a group of poor and needy people will be present to honor him one last time. </p>
          
        </mj-text>
